 acquire it. The Wisdom of Love brings about not only a change in perception—recognizing the existence of the wisdom of love per se—but also the realization that this wisdom is the very foundation of religious wisdom as a whole, rather than a peripheral branch of it. All love derives from a single source: love between man and woman. It is from this source that all other manifestations of love, such as love of God, love of wisdom, and love of one’s fellow, draw their meaning.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aLovexReligious aspectsxJudaism. 0aSex in rabbinical literature. 0aSexxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aSermoneta-Gertel, Shmuel.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161811098540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618110985423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618110985/original  a978-3-11-068814-6  Academic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015c2008d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK